---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 15, 2024',
  tool1: {
    name: '10Web AI',
    slug: '/reviews/10web'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Framer AI',
    slug: '/reviews/framer'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    tenweb: 'Best for WordPress sites and e-commerce',
    framer: 'Best for design quality and marketing pages',
    winner: 'Use 10Web for WordPress, Framer for marketing sites'
  };

---

<Layout title="10Web AI vs Framer AI: WordPress vs Design">

  <!-- WebPage Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: '10Web AI vs Framer AI: WordPress vs Design',
      description: '10Web is WordPress with AI generation. Framer is a design-focused proprietary builder. Comparing them is like comparing a Swiss Army knife to a chef\'s knife.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/10web-vs-framer'
    }}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - Coupon site style -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <!-- Geometric accent -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">10Web AI vs Framer AI:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Totally Different Tools</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              10Web is WordPress with AI generation. Framer is a design-focused proprietary builder. Comparing them is like comparing a Swiss Army knife to a chef's knife—both cut, but for completely different purposes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content wrapper -->
		<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
			<article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
				<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
					<div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
						<p class="text-gray-900">
							<strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
							Use 10Web if you need WordPress, e-commerce, or plugin extensibility.<br />
							Use Framer if you care about design quality, animations, and marketing page performance.<br /><br />
							They're not direct competitors. Pick based on what you're building.
						</p>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The fundamental difference</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						10Web generates WordPress sites. Under the hood, it's standard WordPress—plugins, themes, PHP, MySQL. You get 60,000+ plugins, any WordPress developer can work on it, and you can export/move it anywhere.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Framer generates React-based sites that run on Framer's infrastructure. The code is proprietary. You're locked into their hosting. No plugins. No custom PHP. What you see is what you get—forever.
					</p>

					<div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
						<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
							<div>
								<div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">10Web AI:</div>
								<p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.tenweb}</p>
							</div>
							<div>
								<div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Framer AI:</div>
								<p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.framer}</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
							<strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
						</p>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison</h2>
					<div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
						<table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
							<thead>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
									<th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">10Web AI</th>
									<th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Framer AI</th>
									<th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Generation speed</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">47 seconds</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">2-5 minutes</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Design quality</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Template-based</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Premium custom</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">PageSpeed score</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">78/100</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">95/100</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">E-commerce</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Full WooCommerce</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Basic only</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Export options</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Full WordPress</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$25/month tier</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Plugin ecosystem</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">60,000+ plugins</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">None</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
								</tr>
								<tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Learning curve</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Medium (WordPress)</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Low-Medium</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Tie</td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Monthly cost</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$10-60</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$15-25</td>
									<td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
								</tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
					</div>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where 10Web wins</h2>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Real e-commerce</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Framer has basic e-commerce. 10Web has full WooCommerce—product variants, inventory management, shipping zones, tax calculation, 60+ payment gateways. If you're selling anything beyond simple products, 10Web is the only viable option.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">You can actually leave</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						10Web exports standard WordPress. Move to any host, self-host, hire any WordPress developer. Framer locks you in permanently. Export costs $25/month and the code still depends on Framer's ecosystem.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">The plugin ecosystem</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Need a membership system? WordPress has a plugin. Need advanced SEO? Yoast SEO. Need a forum? bbPress. 10Web gives you access to everything WordPress has built over 20 years. Framer has whatever Framer has built.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Content sites</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						For blogs, news sites, documentation—WordPress is purpose-built. Categories, tags, authors, comments, RSS—all built-in. Framer can do blogs but it's not the primary use case. Content management in 10Web feels natural.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Framer wins</h2>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Design quality</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Framer sites look like they were designed by professionals. Smooth animations, micro-interactions, scroll effects. 10Web sites look like WordPress sites—functional but generic. If aesthetics matter, Framer wins.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Performance</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						My test sites: Framer at 0.8s load time, 10Web at 2.3s. WordPress overhead is real. Framer uses modern web technologies, image optimization, and code splitting by default. 10Web requires optimization work to match Framer's speed.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Marketing page features</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Scroll animations, hover effects, smooth page transitions—Framer excels at marketing sites. These make SaaS landing pages and portfolios feel premium. 10Web can do this but requires plugins or custom CSS.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Simplicity for non-WordPress users</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						If you don't know WordPress, 10Web has learning curves. Themes, plugins, widgets, page builders—it's a lot. Framer is intuitive. Generate, click to edit, publish. Non-technical users find Framer much friendlier.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Real example: Built the same site twice</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						Created a SaaS marketing site on both platforms with identical content:
					</p>

					<div class="my-8 space-y-4">
						<div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
							<div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">10Web AI: 2.5 hours</div>
							<p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
								Generated in 47 seconds. Spent 2 hours fighting with theme settings, plugin conflicts, and slow page loads (2.8s). Had to install caching plugin, image optimizer, and performance plugin to get decent speed. Final result: functional but not beautiful.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
							<div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer AI: 45 minutes</div>
							<p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
								Generated initial version in 3 minutes. Spent 20 minutes refining design and adding animations. 15 minutes tweaking copy and testing mobile. Loaded in 0.9s. Looked premium. Felt fast. Client loved it.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<strong>The lesson:</strong> For marketing sites, Framer is faster to build and better results. For anything complex (e-commerce, memberships, custom functionality), 10Web is the only path.
					</p>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>So which should you use?</h2>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose 10Web if:</h3>
					<ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<li>You're building an e-commerce store (WooCommerce)</li>
						<li>You need plugin functionality WordPress provides</li>
						<li>You want to own your code and export easily</li>
						<li>You're building a content-heavy site (blog, news, docs)</li>
						<li>You have WordPress experience or resources</li>
					</ul>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Framer if:</h3>
					<ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						<li>You're building a portfolio or marketing site</li>
						<li>Design quality and animations matter</li>
						<li>You want fast page loads without optimization work</li>
						<li>You're non-technical and want simplicity</li>
						<li>You don't care about code ownership</li>
					</ul>

					<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
					<div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
						10Web and Framer aren't really competitors. 10Web is WordPress with AI generation—powerful, extensible, familiar, but complex. Framer is a design-focused builder—beautiful, fast, simple, but limited.<br /><br />
						Pick 10Web for functionality and portability. Pick Framer for design and performance. Both are excellent at what they do. The mistake is picking the wrong tool for your use case.
					</p>

					<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
						<a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
							Read 10Web review
						</a>
						<a href={comparisonData.tool2.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
							Read Framer review
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</main>


</Layout>
